generate a second hash value of the file;
cause storage of the second hash value on the blockchain; and
verify contents of the file have not changed based on the second hash value on the blockchain.cause storage of a file in the off-chain datastore;generate a second hash value of the file;cause storage of the second hash value on the blockchain; andverify contents of the file have not changed based on the second hash value on the blockchain.3. The at least one non-transitory computer readable storage medium of claim 1, wherein the instructions cause the one or more processors to at least verify contents of the contract have not changed based on the hash value on the blockchain.4. The at least one non-transitory computer readable storage medium of claim 1, wherein at least one of the blockchain or the transaction is distributed to at least one of the multiple nodes in the IoT network.5. The at least one non-transitory computer readable storage medium of claim 1, wherein the blockchain is a ledger and the contract is a smart contract.6. The at least one non-transitory computer readable storage medium of claim 1, wherein the instructions cause the one or more processors to at least initiate the blockchain.7. The at least one non-transitory computer readable storage medium of claim 1, wherein the instructions cause the one or more processors to at least cause deployment of the blockchain to the multiple nodes in the IoT network.8. The at least one non-transitory computer readable storage medium of claim 1, wherein the instructions cause the one or more processors to at least access the transaction from the IoT network.9. An apparatus comprising:
